Two people were injured when an electrical substation exploded in the Mandeni area on the North Coast on Wednesday afternoon. According to IPSS Medical Rescue spokesperson Paul Herbst, their advanced life support paramedics treated two men with extensive burns. “Upon arrival, paramedics established that an electrical substation had exploded, resulting in two [people] sustaining critical injuries. Paramedics worked to stabilise the men, who both suffered extensive burns.” He said one of the men had to be airlifted to hospital. “The second patient was transported to a local facility under the care of advanced life support paramedics.” The cause of the explosion is currently not known.